snippet.textDisplay: We all have seen the best of the best fall and never get the “eye of the tiger” back. We all say it and see it. I admit, I did too. But knowing the back story of Connor and what he believes about manifesting, affirmations, and the law of attraction....then to see Tony Robbins walk into the octogon, you can believe that this is going to be one of those very rare instances where someone who is a legend becomes a GOD. I am excited to see this man be that person who defies the odds of fighting the demons of self doubt after you have been at the top. You cannot be the greatest forever and that is the facts of life. But the facts of life are also we love the underdog story and we love the comeback story. Watching C-McC (I just made that up) fight is both exciting and gut wrenching. Perhaps like the world watching astronauts land on the moon. As a witness of the times we are so fortunate to see humans like this to inspire us to overcome our own personal battles by comparing ourselves to the greats of human potential. Watching C-McC grow from a hungry young pimply faced boy to a cocky champion and now to a humble warrior is my favorite part. Don;t you agree? #LifeTheresAnAppForThat
